---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import portrait from "@assets/speakers/jago-devreede.jpg";
import location from "@assets/location.jpg";

import Layout from "@layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="banner" style={{ backgroundImage: `url(${location.src})` }}>
    <p>
      Jago de Vreede<br />
      Software engineer at Quintor
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="copy" id="two-column">
    <div class="column" id="fullwidth">
      <h1 id="abstract">Digitizing your old 8mm films with a PI</h1>

      <p>
        Until the late 80's consumers used film like super 8 to record their own films, but not a lot of equipment survived to play them back or people don't want to setup a projector and screen for a few minutes of movie. There are a lot of companies that can scan your movie and put it on a hard disk or DVD. But how hard can it be to do it yourself?
      </p>

      <p>
        After this talk you will know what it takes to digitize your own films code-wise and how to build a rig to facilitate this.
      </p>

      <p>
        Some topics that will be touched upon: using a scanner with a PI, image processing (on a PI), resource management, lessons learned.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column" id="biography">
      <h1>About Jago</h1>

      <p>
        Jago is a software engineer at Quintor. As a software engineer he has seen a broad spectrum of projects and has been working on multiple large-scale educational software and banking projects over the past few years. His work is not exclusive to Java and Scala development â€” he also does front-end development and the integration between these. He is passionate about his work and likes to share his knowledge, having spoken at conferences worldwide.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="column" id="photograph">
      <Image src={portrait} alt="Jago de Vreede" class="photograph" />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
